com.oregonscientific.meep.msm
Class MessageFilter

java.lang.Object
  com.oregonscientific.meep.msm.MessageFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Parcelable
public class MessageFilter
extends Object
implements Parcelable

Structured description of message values to be matched. A MessageFilter can match against operation code, status code, and process in a message.

Filter Rules

A match is based on the following rules. Note that for an IntentFilter to match an Intent, three conditions must hold: the operation code and process code must match, and the status code if specified must match.

Process code matches if the given value match the message process. Note that a MessageFilter with no process code will only match a message that does not have a process code.

Operation code match if the given value match the operation code of the message, or if no operation code was specified in the filter.

Status code match if the given value match the status code of the message received, or if not status code was specified in the filter.

Author:
lam.stanley

match

public final int match(String process,
                       String operation,
                       int status)
Tests whether this filter matches the given data. A match is only successful if process, operation and status code match against the filter.

Parameters:
process - The process to match against Message.getProcess()
operation - The operation to match against Message.getOperation()
status - The status code to match against Message.getStatus()
Returns:
A positive integer or one of the error codes NO_MATCH_PROCESS if the process did not match, NO_MATCH_OPERATION if the operation did not match or NO_MATCH_STATUS if the status code returned did not match.
